g.title: An element with a bottom margin of 30px followed by a sibling element with a top margin of 30px will have their margins collapsed into a total margin of 30px between them.
An element with a top margin of 30px and its first child element with a top margin of 30px will collapse so that the child element's margin collapses with that of its parent.
An element with a bottom margin of 30px and its last child element with a bottom margin of 30px will collapse so that the child element's margin collapses with that of its parent.
An element that doesn't take up space in the flow of the page will have its top and bottom margins collapse to 0.
